Can 良い　Mean the same as 好き？
Have a Question about some Grammar point? Share it with the world!
Post a reply
6 posts
• Page 1 of 1
Can 良い　Mean the same as 好き？
by kentaku_sama » Wed 10.13.2010 3:06 pm I was reading a comment and I saw this sentence:『Holiday's in the﻿ sun』の曲と違ってダークな感じがまた良いね。I couldn't figure out what it meant but when I looked up the sentence　on an online dictionary, I found another sentence:彼にその絵は良いねと言ったのは正直な気持ちだTrans:　When I told him I liked the picture, I really meant it。It said.　This clears it up for me but I need to know　for sure if 良い　Can be used like好きEx: 猫が好き　I like cats猫が良いね　I like cats.　Lit: Cats are good　『Holiday's in the﻿ sun』の曲と違ってダークな感じがまた良いね。　From that as far as I can tell, it seems something like: "Once again like the different dark feeling of the music on Holidays in the sun." Is this correct?
kentaku_sama
Posts: 208Joined: Fri 11.21.2008 2:21 am
Native language: English
Top
Re: Can 良い　Mean the same as 好き？
by micahcowan » Wed 10.13.2010 4:29 pm kentaku_sama wrote:彼にその絵は良いねと言ったのは正直な気持ちだTrans:　When I told him I liked the picture, I really meant itIt's not that いいね can have the same meaning as 好き; it's that the more literal translation of "My telling him: 'that picture's great!', was done with an honest feeling" is obviously a very awkward sentence in English. It's slightly paraphrased, in order to sound like a much more natural English expression.『Holiday's in the﻿ sun』の曲と違ってダークな感じがまた良いね。　From that as far as I can tell, it seems something like: "Once again like the different dark feeling of the music on Holidays in the sun." I'm afraid I donn't understand your English translation, here. As to the meaning of the Japanese, I'd need to see more context to attempt a translation. It seems a bit ambiguous to me, without seeing where it came from. If I had to guess, I'd probably go with something like "[On hearing] the tune "Holiday's in the sun", [something: me? everything?] changed, and my dark mood became good [happy] again."
Micah J Cowan
http://www.JapaneseReader.com
micahcowan
Posts: 249Joined: Fri 08.13.2010 2:08 pmLocation: California, USA
Native language: US English/米語
