Re: Can 良い　Mean the same as 好き？
by Hyperworm » Wed 10.13.2010 5:50 pm If you're saying something is good, you probably like it. So translating 良い as "like" will often be fine and the most natural way to translate. But like micahcowan, I wouldn't say 良い can mean 好き.
